entries.title: ElevenLabs made an AI album to plug its music generator
entries.snippet:
ElevenLabs has released "The Eleven Album," a compilation of AI-generated songs created using its Eleven Music generator and Iconic Voices Marketplace. This project aims to demonstrate how artists can collaborate with AI while maintaining full authorship and commercial rights over their work. Each of the 13 participating artists produced an original track that integrates their signature sound with Eleven Music's capabilities, and they retain 100% of streaming revenue.

The album, available on Spotify and the ElevenLabs website, showcases various musical genres and spoken word pieces. The initiative comes as major record labels like Universal Music Group, Warner Records, and Sony Music Entertainment begin to shift their stance on AI by forging partnerships with AI music platforms such as Suno, Udio, and Klay's ethical AI platform. In contrast to past conflicts over copyright and voice cloning, ElevenLabs promotes a model of ethical AI use by giving artists control and compensation, addressing concerns about unauthorized AI clones impacting musicians' livelihoods.

v.title: Amazon plays catch-up with new Nova AI models to generate voices and video
v.snippet:
Amazon has unveiled new AI innovations aimed at competing with leading technologies like Gemini Live and OpenAI’s Advanced Voice Mode. The highlight is the Nova Sonic voice model, designed for real-time speech processing and natural conversational interactions. Unlike traditional systems that rely on separate components for speech recognition, text conversion, and voice generation, Nova Sonic employs a unified model architecture, enabling more fluid and context-aware responses. It also improves detection of tone for more natural communication. Available on Amazon’s Bedrock developer platform, Nova Sonic targets applications in customer service, healthcare, travel, and education, and is already partially integrated into the new Alexa Plus assistant.

In addition to voice AI, Amazon released Nova Reel 1.1, an update focused on video generation. This upgrade enhances video quality and reduces latency compared to its predecessor. Nova Reel 1.1 can maintain consistent visual styles across several short video segments, allowing creation of cohesive videos up to two minutes long. These developments reflect Amazon’s push to advance in the competitive AI space.

entries.title: Piotr Dabkowski
entries.snippet:
ElevenLabs, a rapidly growing AI startup co-founded by Polish entrepreneurs Piotr Dabkowski and Mateusz Staniszewski, has developed a state-of-the-art voice cloning technology. This tool allows users to generate lifelike voices from short audio samples and supports speech synthesis in 29 languages, making it highly useful for dubbing and voiceover applications. The company, just two years old, is already valued at $1.1 billion and has secured $80 million in funding from investors like Andreessen Horowitz. Major clients include HarperCollins, TIME, and the Washington Post.

The model stands out for its high quality, low latency, and robustness. Dabkowski notes that the technology is approaching a "quality ceiling," where AI-generated voices are indistinguishable from real human ones, raising ethical and security concerns. To address this, ElevenLabs has built-in safeguards such as credit card verification for access, audio generation tracking, and a speech classifier to detect AI-generated content. The company also participates in the U.S. AI Safety Institute's Consortium. Despite these efforts, some users have bypassed protections, emphasizing the ongoing challenge of preventing misuse in the rapidly evolving landscape of generative AI.

entries.title: "Metamorph isn't about replacing the human voice - it's about expanding what's possible when human creativity meets responsible AI": Antares unveils MetaMorph voice modelling plugin
entries.snippet:
Antares Audio Technologies, known for its AutoTune software, has launched a new AI-powered vocal modelling plugin called MetaMorph. This tool allows users to transform the timbre of a vocal performance using one of 12 ethically trained voice models, all based on real, compensated artists. MetaMorph operates locally without requiring cloud processing and enables a wide range of creative uses, such as simulating other singers’ voices or experimenting with non-vocal audio. Six additional voice models are available through integration with the AI voice platform Voice-Swap.

Unlike competitors such as IK Multimedia's ReSing and Dreamtonics' Vocoflex, MetaMorph does not yet allow users to create custom voice models. Antares emphasizes that MetaMorph is designed to complement, not replace, the human voice, reinforcing its commitment to ethical AI music development. The release aligns with their broader stance on responsible AI use in music creation, backed by a signed industry agreement. MetaMorph is priced at $200, with an introductory Black Friday sale offering up to 60% off, including 50% off MetaMorph and the newly updated AutoTune 2026.

entries.title: Adobe's 'Corrective AI' Can Change the Emotions of a Voice-Over
entries.snippet:
Adobe has introduced "Corrective AI," a tool designed to modify the emotional tone of voice-overs, allowing users to adjust inflection and performance without re-recording. Demonstrated at the MAX Sneaks showcase during Adobe’s annual MAX conference, the AI enables users to select from preset emotions to enhance voice recordings. Rather than generating completely artificial speech, Corrective AI refines existing recordings, offering a practical workflow upgrade for creators.

In addition, Adobe presented "Project Clean Take," an AI tool capable of separating a single audio track into up to five distinct elements, like voices, ambient noise, or music, which can be individually adjusted. This is particularly useful for editing out unwanted background sounds or copyrighted music from public recordings. Adobe also showcased AI-generated, contextually appropriate sound effects that are commercially safe, applied via a conversational interface.

These AI features aim to solve real-world challenges for video editors and content creators, streamlining post-production tasks and improving creative control. Many of these experimental tools are expected to be integrated into Adobe's creative software suite in 2026. The announcement underscores the increasing integration of AI in media production and its growing implications for creative professionals, including voice actors.

entries.title: OpenAI deems its voice cloning tool too risky for general release
entries.snippet:
OpenAI has decided not to release its advanced voice cloning tool, Voice Engine, to the general public due to concerns about the potential for misuse, particularly with the global rise in election-related misinformation. Developed in 2022 and capable of generating a realistic voice clone using just 15 seconds of audio, the tool remains in limited use among select partners. Though integrated into services like ChatGPT's text-to-speech and used by companies like Age of Learning and HeyGen for educational and translation applications, OpenAI is opting for a cautious release strategy to encourage discussions about ethical deployment.

OpenAI emphasizes that it requires explicit consent from speakers for use and embeds watermarks in generated audio to track origin. It urges retiring voice-based authentication methods for sensitive information and supports policy development to protect individuals' voices from misuse. While competitors like ElevenLabs already offer similar tools with safeguards, OpenAI's minimal audio requirement and user-friendly interface raise the stakes, prompting the company to prioritize societal resilience and public education over commercial expansion.

entries.title: Michael Caine and Matthew McConaughey partner with ElevenLabs for AI voice cloning
entries.snippet: Oscar-winning actors Michael Caine and Matthew McConaughey have partnered with voice-cloning startup ElevenLabs, allowing the company to replicate their voices using AI technology. Caine praised the collaboration as a way to celebrate, rather than replace, humanity by enhancing storytelling capabilities. McConaughey, a long-time supporter and investor in ElevenLabs, noted that the partnership will also let him deliver content like his newsletter in Spanish. Founded in 2022, New York-based ElevenLabs originally developed its technology for voice dubbing in media, aiming to preserve speaker identity and emotions across languages. Despite its innovations, the company faced misuse issues, including a widely publicized incident where its software was used to impersonate President Joe Biden in a robocall. In response, ElevenLabs introduced stricter security measures and now blocks unauthorized cloning of celebrity voices.
